player.seasonOutlook: Murphy, a 2021 first-round pick who was a frequent starter and reliable scorer last season, injured his left meniscus in early September working out at the Pelicans headquarters. The surgery will keep him out for 10 to 12 weeks, so Murphy could return in November. Last season, he started 65 of 79 games and averaged 14.5 PPG, 3.6 RPG, 1.4 APG and 1.1 SPG in 31.0 MPG. He is also the only Pelicans player in history to have nine 3-pointers in a game more than once. Murphy's ability to contribute to multiple statistical categories is highly coveted and he can be a nice option to round out fantasy rosters.
